<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="376" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,884,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,884,909]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Wings narrow and elongated, slightly wider in central portion; apical area narrow with two rows of cells; pterostigma short. Forewings axillary angle blunt, usually projected. Antennae long, reaching 
<number box="[1321,1331,920,944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1341,1357,920,944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" value="2.0">2</number>
to 
<number box="[1400,1414,920,944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[1424,1436,920,944]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" value="3.0">3</number>
length of forewing. Head wider than thorax. Spur of hind tibiae incurved, as long as 
<number box="[1097,1111,959,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" value="1.0">1</number>
st and 
<number box="[1175,1189,959,983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="376" value="2.0">2</number>
nd tarsomere.
</paragraph>
